      • fromString

        PronounSet fromString(String input)
        Parses a pronoun set in string format.
        Parameters:
        input - the string to parse. Can be formatted in a number of ways:
        • full format as provided by PronounSet.toString()
        • if the set is a registered default (currently he/she/they/any), the PronounSet.subjective pronoun. Note that input is sanitised to ignore all content after a slash, making this method suitable for command processing
        Returns:
        the parsed set
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if a predefined set matching the input cannot be found and if the input is not a valid set

      • parseSets

        Set<PronounSet> parseSets(String... input)
        Parses a string into a collection of pronoun sets. Appropriate for use in commands.
        Returns:
        the parsed sets
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if a set can't be parsed due to either being unknown or censored

      • getAllUserPronouns
